Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->are(a=>'Real');
$p = random(1,9,1);
$q = random(1,9,2);
$p2 = 2*$p;
$num = (2*$p+$q);
$left = Formula("$p/a");
$right = Formula("$q/(2a)");
$expression = $left + $right;
Context("RationalFunction-Strict");
Context()->variables->are(a=>'Real');
$answer = Formula("$num/(2a)");

############################################################
# Body
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML
Given that [`a\neq0\text{,}`] simplify [`\displaystyle{}[$expression]\text{.}`]

[_]{$answer}{10}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
Since the fractions don't have the same denominator, we have to make them have like denominators. Multiply the first fraction by [`\frac{2}{2}\text{.}`]

[```\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
[$expression] \amp = [$left]\cdot \frac{2}{2} + [$right]\\
\amp = \frac{[$p2]}{2a} + [$right]\\
\amp = [$answer]
\end{aligned}
```]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

